      textEn: [
        "Our family had half a mu of open land behind the house. Mother said, \u2018It\u2019s a pity to leave it idle. You all love eating peanuts, so let\u2019s clear it and plant some.\u2019 We siblings were delighted. We bought seeds, turned the soil, sowed, and watered. Within a few months, we actually had a harvest.",
        "Mother said, \u2018Let\u2019s have a harvest festival tonight and invite your father to taste our new peanuts.\u2019 She made several dishes from the peanuts and told us to hold the festival in the thatched pavilion in the back garden.",
        "The sky wasn\u2019t very clear that evening, but Father came anyway \u2014 a rare occasion indeed.",
        "Father asked, \u2018Do you like eating peanuts?\u2019 We answered eagerly, \u2018Yes!\u2019 \u2018Who can name the good things about peanuts?\u2019 Sister said, \u2018Peanuts taste delicious.\u2019 Brother said, \u2018Peanuts can be pressed for oil.\u2019 I said, \u2018Peanuts are inexpensive; anyone can buy and enjoy them. That\u2019s their merit.\u2019",
        "Father said, \u2018Peanuts have many merits, but one is most precious. Their fruit is buried in the ground, unlike peaches, pomegranates, or apples, which hang their bright red and tender green fruit high on branches for all to admire. Peanuts grow low on the ground; even when ripe, you can\u2019t tell at a glance whether they have fruit \u2014 you must dig them up to find out.\u2019",
        "We all agreed, and Mother nodded too.",
        "Father continued, \u2018So you should be like the peanut. It may not look attractive, but it is very useful.\u2019",
        "I said, \u2018Then a person should be useful, not someone who only cares about appearances but is of no benefit to others.\u2019",
        "Father said, \u2018Exactly. That is my hope for you.\u2019",
        "We talked late into the night. The peanut dishes were all gone, but Father\u2019s words were deeply imprinted on my heart."
      ],
