        "Miscellaneous Poems of Jihai\nby Gong Zizhen (Qing)\nThe vitality of the nine provinces depends on wind and thunder;\nten thousand horses all silent is truly lamentable.\nI urge the Lord of Heaven to rouse himself again\nand send down talents without sticking to convention."
